      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can sense the frustration, but don't worry, I'm here to help you navigate this situation. When searching for new flights, it's essential to prioritize your needs, especially since you're trying to get to Singapore as quickly as possible. You should focus on finding flights with the shortest travel time, considering factors like layovers, flight duration, and departure/arrival times.\n\nIt's a good idea to compare prices and schedules across multiple airlines to find the best option for you. You might want to consider booking a flight with a shorter layover or one that departs early in the morning to minimize delays. Some airlines might offer more convenient schedules, like non-stop flights or early morning departures, which could help you reach your destination faster.\n\nYou might also want to check for any travel restrictions or requirements, such as visa requirements or COVID-19 testing, before booking your new flight. And, of course, make sure to read the fine print and understand any cancellation policies or fees associated with your new flight.\n\nBy prioritizing your needs and doing some research, you should be able to find a new flight that gets you to Singapore as quickly as possible. I hope this helps, and I'm here to guide you through the process.",
